{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantProtocol"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"refSink","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VariantRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_ref_sink()"},{"text":" on a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" with a floating reference","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will convert the floating reference into a full reference.  Calling"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" on a non-floating "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" results in an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"additional normal reference being added.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In other words, if the ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is floating, then this call “assumes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"ownership” of the floating reference, converting it to a normal"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reference.  If the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is not floating, then this call adds a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"new normal reference increasing the reference count by one.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All calls that result in a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" instance being inserted into a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"container will call "},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on the instance.  This means","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that if the value was just created (and has only its floating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference) then the container will assume sole ownership of the value"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"at that point and the caller will not need to unreference it.  This","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"makes certain common styles of programming much easier while still"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"maintaining normal refcounting semantics in situations where values"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are not floating.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variantprotocol\/refsink()"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantProtocol\/refSink()"},"abstract":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" uses a floating reference count system.  All functions with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"names starting with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_new_"},{"type":"text","text":" return floating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"references.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"refSink"},{"text":"(